    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> (skins on) lengthways into quarters</p><p>Cut your <strong>potato[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and<strong> sweet potato[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>(skin on) into chips</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-root-veg-chips-and-bangin-ketchup/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped potatoes </strong>and<strong> carrots </strong>to one side of a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 10-15 min or until everything is starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-root-veg-chips-and-bangin-ketchup/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate your<strong> cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-root-veg-chips-and-bangin-ketchup/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> to a small bowl with the <strong>grated cheese,</strong> 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> \u2013 these are your <strong>cheesy breadcrumbs</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-root-veg-chips-and-bangin-ketchup/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the root vegetables are cooking, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong> and <strong>cider vinegar</strong> to a bowl and stir until combined</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>bangin' ketchup</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-root-veg-chips-and-bangin-ketchup/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the root vegetables have softened, remove the tray[s] from the oven and add your <strong>cod fillet[s]</strong> to the other side of the tray[s]</p><p>Top the <strong>cod fillet[s]</strong> with the <strong>cheesy breadcrumbs</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>cheesy crusted cod</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a further 13-15 min or until the fish is cooked through and everything's golden</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-root-veg-chips-and-bangin-ketchup/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the fish is cooking, boil half a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>sweet pea pods </strong>to a pot, cover them with <strong>boiling water</strong> (just enough to cover them), add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until they're tender</p><p>Once tender, drain and return to the pot</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-root-veg-chips-and-bangin-ketchup/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cheesy crusted cod</strong> with the <strong>root</strong> <strong>vegetable chips</strong>, <strong>sweet pea pods</strong> and <strong>bangin' ketchup</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
